      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS CHIT CHAT (8) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (20.30) last time in a Grade 5 at Goulburn. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Has winning claims on her best figures. SCOTT THE POP (1) hit the ground running from out wide and on speed early but faded and swamped late when 7th at this track in Grade 4 company. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Cannot be left out. SCOTT WEDNESDAY (6) jumped from a squeeze box last start but was quickly into stride and led throughout to score (19.60) at this track in a Grade 3 over 340m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and five minor placings to her credit. Expecting another bold showing. CHINESE CHARIOT (2) is worth consideration.",
